whenever we deploy the code in our driver station, the communication is green, robot code is green, and joysticks are green but for some odd reason our robot wont respond to the input?

the controllers are being recognized in the driver station and it detected the movements of the buttons and stuff but there’s no response from the bot. Driver station is giving no errors and code builds and deploys just fine. Any ideas to what could be the problem?

link to our code - GitHub - c4psaic1n/geodecode: 8757 GEODEBOTS code

// The driver’s controller
CommandXboxController m_driverController = new CommandXboxController(OIConstants.kDriverControllerPort);

Then don’t declare JoystickButtons
simply
m_driverController.y().onTrue(whatever command)
